  </Delayed> 
  <CHI_square>
Reduced CHI_square (GEF against evaluations and LOHENGRIN experiments)
FF post-neutron mass distribution
 
Masses with any yield smaller than  0.01% not included.
  </CHI_square>
  <Comments>
Further comments:
 
Yields are given in percent, normalized to 200%.
The lowest yields from this Monte-Carlo calculation
are unavoidably subject to large statistical fluctuations.
 
Uncertainties and covariances or correlation coefficients,
if required, are determined by calculations with perturbed
parameters. They only consider the uncertainties of the
description of the fission process. Uncertainties of more
general ingredients, for example the description of the 
level density, the gamma strength function and others that
are common to all systems are not included. Therefore, the
uncertainties given above are suited for comparing different
systems, but they may be underestimated on an absolute scale.
 
Small shell effects in the symmetric fission channel influence
the relative weight of this channel in the lighter actinides.
Values different from zero were deduced for several nuclei from measured
mass distributions. They are included in the code.
 
  </Comments>
</GEF>
